<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-04T13:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-04T13:40:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1078.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-04T14:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Have persuaded President Bordas to make last appeal to Arias. <hi rend="italic">Petrel</hi> sails tonight with Bordas and Lovaton. I
                            believe surpassing effrontery and egotism of Arias makes agreement out
                            of the question. Bordas will not permit Horacio Vasquez to return under
                            tense circumstances fearing further revolutionary activities on his
                            part. Claimed country must be handled firmly else anarchy will follow.
                            Provisional Government can subdue sanguinary element if you give it
                            means.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>